<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
This species has been taken frequently in baited traps (
<bibRefCitation author="Blankenship, LE" journalOrPublisher="Deep-Sea Research Part I-Oceanographic Research Papers" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="48 - 61" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.dsr.2005.09.006" refId="B31" refString="Blankenship, LE, Yayanos, AA, Cadien, DB, Levin, LA, 2006. Vertical zonation patterns of scavenging amphipods from the Hadal zone of the Tonga and Kermadec Trenches. Deep-Sea Research Part I-Oceanographic Research Papers 53 (1): 48 - 61, DOI: 10.1016/j.dsr.2005.09.006" title="Vertical zonation patterns of scavenging amphipods from the Hadal zone of the Tonga and Kermadec Trenches." url="10.1016/j.dsr.2005.09.006" volume="53" year="2006">Blankenship et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jamieson, AJ" journalOrPublisher="Deep Sea Research Part I: Oceanographic Research Papers" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="49 - 62" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.dsr.2010.11.003" refId="B105" refString="Jamieson, AJ, Kilgallen, NM, Rowden, AA, Fujii, T, Horton, T, Loerz, AN, Kitazawa, K, Priede, IG, 2011. Bait-attending fauna of the Kermadec Trench, SW Pacific Ocean: Evidence for an ecotone across the abyssal-hadal transition zone. Deep Sea Research Part I: Oceanographic Research Papers 58 (1): 49 - 62, DOI: 10.1016/j.dsr.2010.11.003" title="Bait-attending fauna of the Kermadec Trench, SW Pacific Ocean: Evidence for an ecotone across the abyssal-hadal transition zone." url="10.1016/j.dsr.2010.11.003" volume="58" year="2011">Jamieson et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
), and seems also to live a semi-pelagic lifestyle as it has been taken in mid-water trawls (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Birstein, JA" journalOrPublisher="rudy Instituta Okeanologii" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="219 - 257" refId="B25" refString="Birstein, JA, Vinogradov, ME, 1958. . rudy Instituta Okeanologii 27: 219 - 257" volume="27" year="1958">Birstein and Vinogradov 1958</bibRefCitation>
). It appears to be a lower abyssal and hadal endemic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<bibRefCitation author="Dahl, E" journalOrPublisher="Galathea Report" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="211 - 241" refId="B67" refString="Dahl, E, 1959. Amphipoda from depths exceeding 6000 meters. Galathea Report 1: 211 - 241" title="Amphipoda from depths exceeding 6000 meters." volume="1" year="1959">Dahl (1959)</bibRefCitation>
described the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahl" authorityYear="1959" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Bathycallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bathycallisoma" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<pageBreakToken pageId="11" pageNumber="12" start="start">Bathycallisoma</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for his new species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahl" authorityYear="1959" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Bathycallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bathycallisoma pacifica" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bathycallisoma pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Kermadec Trench, placing aff. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1903" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Paracallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paracallisoma" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Paracallisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spec. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schellenberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Reports of the Swedish Deep-Sea Expedition, Zoology" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="182 - 195" refId="B173" refString="Schellenberg, A, 1955. Amphipoda. Reports of the Swedish Deep-Sea Expedition, Zoology 2 (14): 182 - 195" title="Amphipoda." volume="2" year="1955">Schellenberg 1955</bibRefCitation>
from the Puerto Rico Trench in its synonymy. While 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dahl’s">Dahl's</normalizedToken>
publication was in press 
<bibRefCitation author="Birstein, JA" journalOrPublisher="rudy Instituta Okeanologii" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="219 - 257" refId="B25" refString="Birstein, JA, Vinogradov, ME, 1958. . rudy Instituta Okeanologii 27: 219 - 257" volume="27" year="1958">Birstein and Vinogradov (1958)</bibRefCitation>
published an account of the amphipods of the north-western Pacific, including a new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Birstein &amp; Vinogradov" authorityYear="1958" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheirus schellenbergi" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schellenbergi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Scopelocheirus schellenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also with aff. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1903" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Paracallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paracallisoma" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Paracallisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spec. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schellenberg, A" journalOrPublisher="Reports of the Swedish Deep-Sea Expedition, Zoology" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="182 - 195" refId="B173" refString="Schellenberg, A, 1955. Amphipoda. Reports of the Swedish Deep-Sea Expedition, Zoology 2 (14): 182 - 195" title="Amphipoda." volume="2" year="1955">Schellenberg 1955</bibRefCitation>
in its synonymy. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahl, E" journalOrPublisher="Galathea Report" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="211 - 241" refId="B67" refString="Dahl, E, 1959. Amphipoda from depths exceeding 6000 meters. Galathea Report 1: 211 - 241" title="Amphipoda from depths exceeding 6000 meters." volume="1" year="1959">Dahl (1959)</bibRefCitation>
consequently included a footnote in his account, stating that 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schellenberg’s">Schellenberg's</normalizedToken>
specimen should be referred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Birstein &amp; Vinogradov" authorityYear="1958" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheirus schellenbergi" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schellenbergi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Scopelocheirus schellenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which in turn should be recombined as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Birstein &amp; Vinogradov" baseAuthorityYear="1958" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Bathycallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bathycallisoma schellenbergi" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schellenbergi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bathycallisoma schellenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He considered his Kermadec specimen to be a separate species from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Birstein &amp; Vinogradov" baseAuthorityYear="1958" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Bathycallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bathycallisoma schellenbergi" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schellenbergi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bathycallisoma schellenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the shape of the first gnathopod and &quot;some other minor characteristics&quot;. We cannot observe these differences and so prefer to retain 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahl" authorityYear="1959" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Bathycallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bathycallisoma pacifica" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bathycallisoma pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Birstein &amp; Vinogradov" baseAuthorityYear="1958" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Bathycallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bathycallisoma schellenbergi" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schellenbergi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bathycallisoma schellenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, thereby agreeing with most subsequent authors.
</paragraph>
